RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 13600. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: Kennedy Brent A Kennedy Susan K and Kennedy Jr William

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHONEW raced three wide in range in early stages, swung three to four wide into the lane, roused for more in upper stretch, responded willingly and kicked clear. RING BEARER tracked the leader along the inside into the turn, hustled up along the rail heading into the lane, steadily edged up closer, took over the lead from tiring HUEY DUEY then got outkicked by the winner. HUEY DUEY broke on top , cleared and crossed over to the inside shortly after the start, settled nicely on top and held a comfortable lead around the turn, came two to three wide into the lane and asked for more, fought on until the sixteenth pole then got overtaken by the top two finishers. DANCIN ROCKET raced two in contention in early stages, came under a ride two wide entering the lane and responded evenly. LAMELO lacked speed and raced in the back, swung three to four wide into the lane, angled in a couple paths and lacked a rally. FITZEA raced off the second flight around the turn, swung four to five wide into the lane and had no response.

ENTRY.NAME: Fitzea
ENTRY.OWNER: Zieser Dave and Black Oak Farm
ENTRY.COMMENT: off 2nd flight, 4-5wd top stretch, no response

ENTRY.NAME: Lamelo
ENTRY.COMMENT: in back, 3-4wd upper, angled in, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Ring Bearer
ENTRY.COMMENT: track leader, inside bid, brief lead, outkicked

ENTRY.NAME: Dancin Rocket
ENTRY.COMMENT: in contention, 2wd bid into lane, no kick

ENTRY.NAME: Whonew
ENTRY.COMMENT: in range 3wd, 3-4wd bid into lane, responded willingly, clear

ENTRY.NAME: Huey Duey
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, overtaken 1/16p

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEMEANSBIZNESS was forwardly placed in opening stages and stalked the leader into the turn, hustled up two wide entering the lane, responded willingly under pressure and finished going away. DAMASCUS GATE sped to the lead soon after the start and set the pace up the backstretch, continued clear on top around the turn, saved ground entering the lane, got overtaken by the winner in the final furlong and held place. RAISIN RAISIN raced in contention off the top two leaders, hustled along three wide into the drive, roused forward into closer contention and dug in to capture show. OLIVE OYL raced in range between rivals in the early going, hustled up leaving the turn, drifted out five wide entering the lane, ran on and got nipped for show. KAYLA was not too far back in early stages and saved ground along the inside, angled out leaving the turn, sustained a four wide bid in the lane and just missed show.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 14700. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 22, 2022. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLASSIC BET settles nicely and stalked the leaders up the backstretch, tracked three wide around the turn, came four wide into the lane responded willingly when called upon, kicked in gear and finished going away. CHICAGO CHROME dueled outside of HERITAGE PARK in early stages, continued to battle around the turn, could not match strides for the lead in upper stretch but stayed on for a share. TOO LATE was forwardly placed entering the turn, made a bid for command near the quarter pole, continued in range to the furlong marker then flattened out. HOLIDAY TICKET raced off the early pace, saved ground along the inside, shifted out four wide in upper stretch and gained on show. HUNKA BURNING LOVE raced in the back, saved ground around the turn and never threatened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 79. Handicap Purse 50225. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD, REGISTERED IOWA BREDS. Free nominations by Saturday, May 13th. Weights: Sunday, May 14th. Starters to be named by the usual time of closing. Supplemental nominations will be weighted at the time of en try. Preference will be given to high weights. Equal weights preference will be determined by total earnings in 2022-23 at the time of entry. (This race is not considered a sweepstakes).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLAZE AWAY N HIDE stalked the leader along the inside up the backstretch, was patiently ridden awaiting room around the far turn, continued in tight quarters along the rail, slipped through along the rail near the eighth pole, dug in under a drive, gained command and edged away. BOSSY MOMENT was allowed to settle off the pace in early stages, picked up the tempo three to four wide late on the far turn, swung five wide into the lane, kicked in gear under firm handling, rallied and got up for place. MY GOLDEN DAY tracked the pace three wide up the backstretch, loomed up three wide near the quarter pole, briefly vied for command mid-stretch then gave way grudgingly. ANGEL'S MELODY took command shortly after the start and set the pace up the backstretch, continued to hold a slim lead over challengers at the quarter pole, came 2wd into the lane, fought back when confronted by rail running winner then weakened near the final sixteenth. SAMIRA stalked the early leaders, moved up two wide near the lead at the quarter pole, sustained response into the lane then gave way in the final furlong. KELA'S TURN raced near midpack in the early going, was ridden along two wide around the turn, failed to advance and weakened in the lane. JUST LIKE TRISTA was a step sluggish away from the gate and continued in the back, continued off the pace, swung five wide into the lane and never menaced. REBEL RISING raced off the pace, hustled along five wide into the lane and had no response.
